node.text: From reefs to ridges, explore the beauty of the Philippines through the eyes of the locals. While 2020 has been a year of change for travel, the Philippines is excited to invite local visitors to explore the beautiful islands. The #BDTeam had the pleasure of working with @tourism_phl to highlight beautiful places around the Philippines. The opportunities for exploration are endless-from the Hundred Island National Park in Pangasinan to exploring the Suba and Culili Sand Dunes in Ilocos Norte.

node.text:
With an incredibly rich history, being an “Egyptian” can have many facets especially when it comes to creativity. Today, we’re sharing a unique story dedicated to any creative who intends to carve their own path no matter the circumstances. 

“It’s proof that the end product most of the time doesn’t pan out the way you expect it. And its by having expectations that you hinder your potential.” - @matiasderada

Watch this beautiful film on Beautiful Destinations Youtube channel. 🇪🇬

🎥 @matiasderada #BDTeam

Bristol Bay, one of Alaska’s most treasured natural wonders, is under threat. @world_wildlife 

It’s home to an irreplaceable ecosystem and one of the last salmon strongholds. Not only that, its iconic wildlife has sprung up a sustainable tourism industry which effects thousands of Alaskan livelihoods.

All of this is under threat if the Pebble Mine moves forward. The recent approval of the environmental impact statement has made it clear that our voices need to be heard. 

Nature and people can’t live without fresh water, and Bristol Bay is the lifeblood that sustains every species calling the region home. 

On a recent trip to Alaska, the #BDTeam and WWF Ambassador, @jeremyjauncey, learned firsthand about the conservation community’s fight against Pebble Mine.

node.text: As New York City starts to open back up, we wanted to take a moment to reflect on the efforts of heroes in the hospitality industry who have been helping our frontline workers. @fsnewyork was the first hotel in New York City to open its door to our frontline workers and provide them with a safe haven to stay during such an uncertain time. They quickly transformed the hotel into a near medical-grade facility. Over 300 medical workers called @fsnewyork home during this time as they were provided rooms free of charge. This allowed them to keep their own families safe as they focused on their work and taking care of patients. ❤️ (🎥: @loganlambert 📸: @loganstrongarms 📍: Four Seasons Hotel New York)

node.text:
Adventures with dad via @world.from.my.eyes. 👴 “One of the best trips of my life was when I went to Antarctica with my father. My father was way more active than I was. He did everything including hiking on glaciers, camping while it was snowing, and finally being on the top deck when we were stuck on 60 ft waves passing through Drake Passage (the roughest seas in the world).” 💙

While it’s easy to get caught up in today’s fast-paced world, it’s important to spend quality time with loved ones—like embarking on that once-in-a-lifetime adventure in Antarctica.

Where’s your dream family getaway? 🗺

📽 @world.from.my.eyes
📍 Antarctica
🎶 James Horner - Hymn to the Sea

The biggest smile on earth via @condorexpresssb and drone pilot @adam_ernster. 🐋 Reminiscent of a submarine in this video, the colossal blue whale can grow to more than 100 feet long and weigh over 150 tons. 🤯

This footage was shot in the Santa Barbara Channel of California, which is home to over 27 different species of whales and dolphins that visit throughout the year. It's also the prime northern feeding ground for blue whales and humpback whales from May through November. 🇺🇸

Have you ever gone whale watching before? 👀

📽 @condorexpresssb & @adam_ernster
📍 Santa Barbara, California, USA

Imagine setting your eyes on @timulrich.pix's view of Blausee, where crystal-clear waters, multi-colored trees, and soft rays of light paint a picture of a surreal, magical forest. 😌

One of the best-known mountain lakes in Switzerland, Blausee is nestled in the midst of a vast 20-hectare nature park. Its landscape was actually formed by a rockslide, which led to the creation of the lake. The area features walking paths and picnic spots, making it a perfect choice for a refreshing escape amidst nature. 🇨🇭

Are you in dire need of a nature getaway lately? What kind of destination have you been dreaming about? 💭

📽 @timulrich.pix 
📍 Blausee, Switzerland
🎶 Spiritual Gardens - Natural Beauty

If you're curious to see more, check out Hunter's adventures on his YouTube channel! How's this as a ride for your daily commute? 🤯🔥

📽 @hunterkowald
📍 Times Square, New York, USA

Check out @hobopeeba's perspective of the most jaw-dropping pool in the world. If you're looking for the finest rooftop spaces in London, feast your eyes on this world-famous Sky Pool that seems to float in the air. 🏴󠁧󠁢󠁥󠁮󠁧󠁿

Located in the Nine Elms district, this exclusive 25-meter-long pool connects two blocks of apartments. Built by structural engineers Eckersley O'Callaghan and designed by HAL Architects, it's known as the world's first floating transparent 'sky pool'. 💦

Did you know this pool existed in London and would you take a dip in it? 😄

📽 @hobopeeba
📍 London, England
🎶 Måneskin - Beggin'

Finding pockets of tranquility with @justkay. 😌 Hidden deep in the Chiapas rainforest of Mexico, the Arco Del Tiempo features a gorge so narrow that its clifftops graze each other and close the gap. To get to this beautiful place, you need to walk about 8 kilometers through a thick jungle. 🌳

In this fast-paced world, it's important to slow down, focus on the essentials, and steady the flow of your life—may it be by taking a break, going on a remote getaway, or simply saying 'no' to things that don't serve you. 💭

Did you know this place existed in Mexico and would you go here? 🇲🇽

📽 @justkay
📍 Arco Del Tiempo, Mexico 
🎶 Inception: Time - Orchestra Version (Live) - Hans Zimmer, Rusanda Panfili, Eliane Correa, Vienna Radio Symphony Orchestra, Martin Gellner

The best adventures with a furry friend at @visitrasalkhaimah. 🐕 Wadi Shawka is one of Ras Al Khaimah's most sought-after hiking destinations known for its scenic and invigorating trail. 🇦🇪

Only an hour-long drive from Dubai, Ras Al Khaimah holds plenty of adventure in store, especially for hiking lovers! Wadi Shawka is a relatively easy hike and can be suitable for most age groups and fitness levels. Best of all, it offers spaces for picnics and overnight camping. ⛺️

The best months to visit Wadi Shawka are from November to March when the temperature is comfortable, so mark your calendars! Have you seen this side of UAE and would you love to hike here?

📽 @tomjauncey
🐕 @hk9uc & @pack_dxb
📍 Wadi Shawka, @visitrasalkhaimah, UAE
